{{italictitle}} {{Infobox book | name = An Inconvenient Sequel: Truth to Power | title_orig = | translator = | image = File:An inconvenient sequel book.jpg | caption = | author = [[Al Gore]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = | language = | series = | subject = [[Global warming]] | genre = | publisher = [[Rodale Books]] | pub_date = July 25, 2017 | media_type = | pages = 320 | isbn = 978-1-63565-108-9 | isbn_note = (paperback) | dewey = | congress = | oclc = | preceded_by = [[Our Choice]] | followed_by = }} '''''An Inconvenient Sequel: Truth to Power: Your Action Handbook to Learn the Science, Find Your Voice, and Help Solve the Climate Crisis''''' is a book by former [[Vice President of the United States|Vice President]] and [[environmental activist]] [[Al Gore]], written in conjunction with his 2017 documentary film, ''[[An Inconvenient Sequel: Truth to Power]].'' The book is a sequel to his 2006 book ''[[An Inconvenient Truth (book)|An Inconvenient Truth]]'', published concurrently with his [[An Inconvenient Truth|documentary of the same name]]. It was published on July 25, 2017 by [[Rodale Books]].<ref name=Rodale>{{cite web|url=https://www.rodalebooks.com/inconvenient-sequel/|title=An Inconvenient Sequel: Truth to Power|author=<!--Not stated-->|date=2017|website=rodalebooks.com|publisher=Rodale, Inc.|access-date=2018-02-27|quote=}}</ref>
==Synopsis== The book is intended to encourage and inform readers on how they can help fight [[global warming|anthropogenic global warming]] and [[climate change]], and is a more in-depth analysis than the film. The book describes how humans have further damaged the environment since the release of ''An Inconvenient Truth'', and makes more predictions about what will happen in the near future if humans fail to act. The book also describes advancements that have been made so far in the effort against global warming, such as developments in [[alternative energy]] sources. The book explores other aspects of the climate crisis, such as [[climate change denial]] and the [[campaign finance in the United States|corporate influence of money in politics]], and ends by reasoning that it is not too late to solve the crisis.
