The '''Governance Initiative for Rights & Accountability in Forest Management (GIRAF)''' is a project executed in [[Ghana]] with funds from the [[European Union]] (EU) and its partners CARE Denmark, CIVIC Response, [[Friends of the Earth Ghana|Friends of the Earth-Ghana]] and Centre for Indigenous Knowledge.

