The '''Solano''' is a south to south-easterly [[wind]] in the southern sector of [[Spain]]. In the spring and summer, from June to September, it carries hot, dry, suffocating weather over [[La Mancha]] and the [[Andalusia]]n plain with the cities of [[Sevilla]] and [[Cádiz]]. It is also known as the [[Levant_(wind)|Levant]].

