The '''Vinton Furnace State Experimental Forest''' and Raccoon Ecological Management Area (REMA) is a [[list of Ohio state forests|state forest]] in [[Vinton County, Ohio|Vinton County]], [[Ohio]], [[United States]]. It comprises 15,849 acres, the largest remaining intact block of forest in Ohio still available for permanent protection. Since 2000, data collected at the forest has been cited in nearly 200 academic articles.<ref name=ODNR1>{{cite web |url =http://forestry.ohiodnr.gov/vintonfurnace |title =Vinton Furnace State Forest |first = |last = |date = |website =ODNR Division of Forestry |publisher =Ohio Department of Natural Resources |access-date =Aug 11, 2015 }}</ref>
